title: Moscow rampage reveals ambition, deadly reach of ISIS successor groups
description: Before Friday’s massacre, ISIS spinoffs were on the march from North Africa to South Asia. One group appears laser-focused on terrorist attacks abroad.

title: Terror suspects appear in court in Russia showing signs of torture and abuse
description: Russian authorities arrested four men, identified as citizens of Tajikistan, for allegedly attacking the Crocus City Hall concert venue, and the Islamic State claimed responsibility, but Russian media has blamed Ukraine.

title: Israeli delegations visit Washington amid U.S. misgivings over Gaza war
description: Israelis are focusing on areas of agreement with the United States ahead of the visit, but U.S. officials are increasingly expressing concern over the humanitarian crisis in Gaza.

title: Friends, family, acquaintances: What would have happened to them if Gaza was home?
description: The numbers coming out of Gaza can be hard to comprehend. So let’s apply it to a smaller scale.

title: What we know so far about the deadly attack on a Moscow concert hall
description: The incident at Crocus City Hall, for which ISIS has claimed responsibility, has been described as the worst terrorist attack in Russia in 20 years.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Two Israeli delegations visit U.S. as Harris warns against Rafah attack
description: Defense Minister Yoav Gallant’s visit comes as another Israeli team is in Washington to hear U.S. concerns about Israel’s plans for a ground operation in crowded Rafah.

title: The U.S. and Israel have a ‘major credibility problem’
description: U.S. officials are carrying water on the world stage for an increasingly unpopular Israeli government, while fitfully trying behind the scenes to cajole it down a different path.
